Pyspark is the py api for apache spark for big data processing and analytics.

it gives  powerful distributed computing to efficiently process large datasets across clusters.

widely used in data analysis, machine learning and real-time processing.

PySpark = Python + Apache Spark

Apache Spark is a powerful engine used to process huge amounts of data (think GBs, TBs, even PBs).
PySpark is just a way to use that engine using Python instead of Scala/Java.

How pyspark works:
1. Drivers and Workers
2. Distributed processing

Instead of:

Process all data on 1 machine ❌

PySpark does:

Split data → process on many machines → combine result ✅

Core Components of PySpark
1. SparkSession(Entry Point)
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession

spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("MyApp").getOrCreate()

2. Data Structures
